= Pure Ruby PostgreSQL interface

This is a library to access PostgreSQL from Ruby without the need of any C
library.

== Author and Copyright

Copyright (c) 2004 by Michael Neumann (mneumann@ntecs.de). 
Released under the same terms of license as Ruby.

== Homepage

http://rubyforge.org/projects/ruby-dbi

== Quick Example

  > gem install postgres-pr
  > irb -r rubygems 

Then in the interactive Ruby interpreter type (replace DBNAME and DBUSER
accordingly):

  require 'postgres-pr/connection'
  c = Connection.new('DBNAME', 'DBUSER')
  c.query('SELECT 1+2')                  # => [["3"]]
